    "body": "Fixes #34723.\r\n\r\nOn macOS with `REDUCE_EXPORTS`, Cap'n Proto RPC reports `remote exception: unknown non-KJ exception of type: kj::Exception` instead of the actual exception message. This happens because `type-context.h` re-throws a stored `kj::Exception` with a raw `throw` from bitcoin-node code, where `kj::Exception` typeinfo has hidden visibility (due to `REDUCE_EXPORTS` setting `-fvisibility=hidden`). The hidden typeinfo in the executable is not coalesced with `libkj.dylib`'s copy by the macOS dynamic linker, so `getCaughtExceptionAsKj()`'s `catch (kj::Exception& e)` fails and falls through to `catch (...)`.\r\n\r\nThe fix replaces `throw kj::mv(*exception)` with `kj::throwRecoverableException(kj::mv(*exception))`, which routes the throw through `libkj.dylib` where it gets wrapped in `ExceptionImpl` with consistent typeinfo. This is the same pattern Cap'n Proto uses internally in `kj/async-inl.h` when re-throwing stored exceptions from promises.\r\n\r\nAlso removes the test workaround added in 8fe91f3719 that accepted the degraded error message on Darwin.\r\n\r\n**Tested:** `interface_ipc_mining.py` passes on macOS (arm64) with `REDUCE_EXPORTS=ON`. Verified that without this change, the test fails with the exact error described in the issue.",
