      ],
      "message": "ipc: fix exception type visibility with REDUCE_EXPORTS on macOS\n\nUse kj::throwRecoverableException() instead of a raw throw when re-throwing a stored kj::Exception in the IPC worker thread exception handler.\n\nA raw `throw kj::mv(*exception)` throws from bitcoin-node code, where kj::Exception typeinfo has hidden visibility (due to REDUCE_EXPORTS setting -fvisibility=hidden).\n\nWhen Cap'n Proto's getCaughtExceptionAsKj() in libkj.dylib tries to catch it, the hidden typeinfo in the executable is not coalesced with libkj's copy by the macOS dynamic linker, so the catch falls through to the generic \"unknown non-KJ exception\" handler.\n\nthrowRecoverableException() routes the throw through libkj.dylib itself, wrapping it in ExceptionImpl with consistent typeinfo. This matches the pattern Cap'n Proto uses internally (see kj/async-inl.h).\n\nAlso removes the macOS test workaround added in 8fe91f3719 that accepted the degraded error message, since the underlying issue is now fixed.\n\nFixes: bitcoin/bitcoin#34723",
